In this repository, you would have a quick understanding of what we have done for each sprint and the feedback of each sprint:
Sprint 1: 
Sprint planning: The goal is to make an English learning APP for new students to use. We plan to develop English word Lists, speaking training part, listening training part and a forum.
Sprint Review: Feedback from prof.Kaveh: Good but listening part is too general -- should help them adapt the accents of different countries.

Sprint 2:
Sprint Planning: The goal is to polish and fix bugs. Givem that clients come on Tuesday, so we don't plan to do any new features in this short sprint (2 days)
Sprint Review: Feedback from cliens: Good but pay attention to the copyright of materials. In addition, more interactive content should be presented to engage students in English learning journey.

Sprint 3:
Sprint Planning: The goal is to solve the problems left in sprint 1&2. So we manage to add more copyright content and add ted speech as part of listening material.
In addition, more interactive content will be presented for example: A computer game for learning English vocabulary, a group discussion functionalities, ranking lists and pet adoption system. 
